      "question": "If the circumference of a circle is $176\\text{ cm}$, then its radius is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the formula for circumference $C = 2\\pi r$.",
          "Substitute $C = 176$ and $\\pi = \\frac{22}{7}$.",
          "Solve for $r$."
        ],
        "derivation": "176 = 2 \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times r \\implies 176 = \\frac{44}{7} \\times r \\implies r = \\frac{176 \\times 7}{44} = 4 \\times 7 = 28\\text{ cm}"
      },
